Incorrect. <br>
Militia (n)<br>
1.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp An army composed of ordinary citizens rather than professional soldiers.<br>
2.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A military force that is not part of a regular army and is subject to call for service in an emergency.<br>
3.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The whole body of physically fit civilians eligible by law for military service.<br>
<br>
Source: The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, Fourth Edition<br>
